# AKOS UAT Discipline

Use this rule whenever authoring, reviewing, or amending a **closure UAT
report** for any initiative or wave-close in this workspace. Codifies
operator decision **D-IH-86-CW** (operator-ratified the
[`UAT_DISCIPLINE.md`](../../docs/references/hlk/v3.0/Admin/O5-1/People/canonicals/UAT_DISCIPLINE.md)
charter → active promotion at I86 Wave R+1, 2026-05-24). Mechanical
companion to that canonical + to the paired SOP
[`SOP-PEOPLE_UAT_GOVERNANCE_001.md`](../../docs/references/hlk/v3.0/Admin/O5-1/People/canonicals/SOP-PEOPLE_UAT_GOVERNANCE_001.md)
+ paired runbook
[`scripts/validate_uat_report.py`](../../scripts/validate_uat_report.py).

This rule does **not** define the doctrine — that lives in the canonical.
This rule names the mechanical bar that future agents and operators
inherit by default when minting any closure-UAT artefact.

## When this rule applies

A closure-UAT report is in scope for this rule when **any** of:

- The report is named `uat-*.md` and lives under
  `docs/wip/planning/**/reports/`.
- The report's `verdict:` frontmatter field is set (any of
  `PASS` / `PASS-WITH-FOLLOWUP` / `FAIL` / `PENDING-OPERATOR-WALK`).
- The report is the closure-evidence row for a wave inside a
  cluster-coordinator master-roadmap (I86 precedent; future analogous
  coordinators).
- The report is the closure-evidence row for an INITIATIVE_REGISTRY
  status flip from `active` → `complete` / `superseded`.
- The parent initiative's master-roadmap §"Closure criteria" cites the
  report path as the gating artefact.

Reports NOT in scope (rule no-ops):

- Pre-2026-05-19 UAT reports (per [`UAT_DISCIPLINE.md`](../../docs/references/hlk/v3.0/Admin/O5-1/People/canonicals/UAT_DISCIPLINE.md)
  §"Migration posture for pre-2026-05-19 initiatives" — forward-only bar;
  historical reports stay exempt unless amended).
- One-off `reports/checkpoints/sc-*.md` agent self-checkpoints (per
  [`akos-agent-checkpoint-discipline.mdc`](akos-agent-checkpoint-discipline.mdc)
  §"Agent self-checkpoint contract") — not closure UAT.
- Operator-internal scratchpads + planning notes.

## RULE 1 — 11-section structure is mandatory (binding for forward-only reports)

Every in-scope closure-UAT report MUST contain the 11 sections in the
canonical's §8.5 order, even when a section collapses to a one-line N/A
statement. The 11 sections are:

1. Closure summary (TL;DR; J-OP-optimised; <30s read).
2. Closure-criteria verification (per `master-roadmap.md` §"Closure
   criteria"; reproducible commands per row).
3. Mechanical evidence (validator outputs + pytest counts + tsc/lint
   counts + browser-evidence pattern when in scope).
4. Per-dimension findings (multi-column when initiative has multiple
   acceptance dimensions).
5. D-IH-86-D mechanical cross-check (mandatory for I86 cluster siblings;
   N/A for standalone initiatives).
6. SOP + runbook pair (mandatory when initiative shipped a process_list
   row; AC-HUMAN + AC-AUTOMATION acceptance criteria per
   `akos-executable-process-catalog.mdc` Rule 1 §5).
7. Risk-register closure (per `R-IH-NN-N` row status).
8. Decision close-outs (per `D-IH-NN-X` row activation + reversibility).
9. Closure registry edits (mechanical; INITIATIVE_REGISTRY +
   DECISION_REGISTER + OPS_REGISTER after-states).
10. Verdict + 7-item operator sign-off checklist (per
    `akos-agent-checkpoint-discipline.mdc` §"Operator pause point
    contract").
11. Cross-references (parent master-roadmap + decision-log +
    risk-register + files-modified + governing rules).

Section headers accept BOTH compact form (`## 1 — Closure summary`) and
verbose form (`## Section 1 — Closure summary`) per the I86 Wave R
precedent. Dashes accepted: em-dash (—), en-dash (–), hyphen (-), colon
(:), or omitted. The validator's regex enforces both forms.

## RULE 2 — Frontmatter schema is mandatory (binding for forward-only reports)

Every in-scope closure-UAT report MUST carry the following frontmatter
fields per UAT_DISCIPLINE.md §8.5 §"Mandatory frontmatter fields":

- **`verdict:`** one of `PASS` / `PASS-WITH-FOLLOWUP` / `FAIL` /
  `PENDING-OPERATOR-WALK`. Closures cannot be ambiguous about whether the
  gate cleared.
- **`closure_decision_source:`** `agent_inline_default` (per Time-box
  recovery per [`akos-inline-ratification.mdc`](akos-inline-ratification.mdc)
  §"Time-box recovery") / `operator_explicit` / `n/a`.
- **`ratifying_decisions:`** YAML list of every `D-IH-<NN>-<X>` row this
  UAT evidences (including the closure decision when applicable).
- **`linked_runbooks:`** YAML list of every `scripts/<name>.py` runbook
  the parent initiative shipped (per
  [`akos-executable-process-catalog.mdc`](akos-executable-process-catalog.mdc)
  Rule 1 SOP+runbook pairing).
- **`verdict_history:`** YAML list — mandatory when the report is an
  amendment of a prior version (per I77 P3-P4 amendment precedent +
  D-IH-86-BW Wave M.5 amendment precedent); optional otherwise.
- **`last_review:`** ISO date `YYYY-MM-DD`; gates the forward-only
  enforcement watershed (2026-05-19).

**Quality Fabric specialty canonicals** that promote `charter → active`
via a field-test window MUST also carry the machine-readable
[`field_test_window:`](../../akos/hlk_uat_report.py) frontmatter block
(SSOT shape: `akos.hlk_uat_report.CanonicalFieldTestWindow` Pydantic
model). This is binding for any specialty canonical whose promotion
ratifying decision opts for META4-b shape (clean-PASS-with-explicit-
field-test-window per D-IH-86-CW). UAT_DISCIPLINE.md is the first
instantiation; future specialty promotions (INTER_WAVE_REGRESSION
status promotion + INDEX_INTEGRITY status promotion + PWF_GOVERNANCE
status promotion + others) inherit the schema. Required sub-fields per
the Pydantic model: `open_date` + `open_decision_id` + `open_wave` +
`close_target_wave` + `close_target_date_estimate` +
`revocation_decision_id_template` + `monitoring_obligation_owner` +
`monitoring_obligation_co_owner` + `promotion_criteria` (≥1
conjunctive PASS clause; codes match `FTW-<DISC>-NN-<SLUG>`) +
`revocation_triggers` (≥1 disjunctive demotion trigger; codes match
`FTW-<DISC>-RT-NN-<SLUG>`) + `status` (one of `open` / `closing` /
`closed` / `revoked`) + optional `last_observation_*` triple (bumped
at each FTW observation wave-close).

The `field_test_window:` block makes the monitoring obligation
**discoverable + queryable** by tooling — agents authoring observation
entries (e.g. §10.1 / §10.2 / §10.3 of the specialty canonical) MUST
bump the `last_observation_*` triple in the same commit so the
frontmatter stays the source of truth. Burying field-test metadata in
prose only is a recurring anti-pattern (operator's META4-b feedback
2026-05-24 verbatim: *"i was really worried that the UAT would get
shallow or not governed or not properly followed"*); the frontmatter
block exists specifically to prevent it.

## RULE 3 — PASS-WITH-FOLLOWUP requires `verdict_followup_rationale` (binding from D-IH-86-CX promotion)

Per the 12th Quality Fabric specialty mint (D-IH-86-CX —
`PASS_WITH_FOLLOWUP_GOVERNANCE_DISCIPLINE.md`; operator-ratified at
meta5-c full-specialty-mint), any UAT report carrying
`verdict: PASS-WITH-FOLLOWUP` MUST also carry a
`verdict_followup_rationale:` frontmatter field naming the followup-class
(per the canonical's §3 enum: `monitoring-obligation` /
`deferred-work-with-tracker` / `convention-class-followup` / `mechanical-
recovery-with-eta` / `escalation-to-blocker-tracker`) + the follow-up
artifact path (tracker / OPS row / blocker tracker) + the closure-target
ETA when applicable.

This rule operationalises the operator's META4-b ratification: PASS-WITH-
FOLLOWUP is permitted but must NEVER hide deferred-work-as-false-PASS.
Validator finding code `UAT-FM-11-PWF-WITHOUT-RATIONALE` enforces this
at FAIL severity for forward-only reports.

## RULE 4 — Validator self-test wired into pre_commit (binding from D-IH-86-CW promotion)

The runbook `scripts/validate_uat_report.py --self-test` mode verifies
the Pydantic SSOT models + section regex set load + the 5 fixture
constructors return well-formed models. The self-test runs at every
`py scripts/verify.py pre_commit` invocation via
[`config/verification-profiles.json`](../../config/verification-profiles.json)
`validate_uat_report_self_test` step +
[`scripts/release-gate.py`](../../scripts/release-gate.py)
`run_uat_report_validation`.

The full sweep (`--all` or `--report <path>`) runs at **closure-UAT
mint time** + at **3-wave field-test window monitoring** (per the
operator's META4-b ratification) — NOT at every pre_commit (which would
re-scan dozens of historical reports every commit). The self-test is
the always-on circuit-breaker; the full sweep is the event-triggered
gate.

Per D-IH-86-CW INFO → FAIL ramp (aligned with the
`field_test_window:` lifecycle on the canonical):

- **Wave R+1 (this mint; `field_test_window.status: open`):** self-test
  PASS at pre_commit; full sweep runs at the closure-UAT mint commit.
  Validator default mode emits findings at FAIL severity (strict v1
  forward-only-by-date), but the wave-close governance honours the
  field-test window: PWF dispositions of validator findings count as
  field-test signal, not blocker. Promotion criteria
  FTW-UAT-01..FTW-UAT-04 are the conjunctive PASS clauses being tested.
- **Wave S close (`status: open`; `last_observation_wave: S`):** mint a
  closure UAT against this bar. Author bumps
  `field_test_window.last_observation_*` triple in the same commit;
  records whether any of FTW-UAT-RT-01..FTW-UAT-RT-03 triggers fired.
- **Wave T close (`status: open`; `last_observation_wave: T`):** same
  observation cadence. Trend across S → T informs the window's verdict.
- **Wave U close (`status: open` → `closing`):** entry to the final
  observation wave flips `status: closing`. Operator sign-off at the
  Wave U closure UAT then flips to `closed` (durable promotion) OR
  `revoked` (forced demotion via D-IH-86-CW-revoke decision per the
  template; specialty falls back to `status: charter`).
- **Wave U+1 or later (`status: closed`):** bar promotes to release-gate
  INFO advisory at every pre_commit (not just mint commit); validator
  findings ≤ 2 across 3+ consecutive waves = trigger for full FAIL
  promotion at release-gate.

## RULE 5 — Findings disposition via inline-ratify 5-option enum (binding)

Every WARN or FAIL finding from the validator MUST be dispositioned via
an inline `AskQuestion` gate per
[`akos-inline-ratification.mdc`](akos-inline-ratification.mdc) +
[`inline-ratify-craft`](../skills/inline-ratify-craft/SKILL.md), using
the 5-option enum codified in UAT_DISCIPLINE.md §6 + this rule's RULE 5:

1. **rework-now** (default for FAIL on RULE 1 / RULE 2 frontmatter
   gaps).
2. **amend-followup-rationale** (default when FAIL is
   `UAT-FM-11-PWF-WITHOUT-RATIONALE`; surfaces the missing rationale
   as an inline-ratify on which PWF class applies; rationale written
   inline; verdict stays PWF).
3. **defer-OPS** (default for WARN on conditional sections;
   followup-class encoded as `deferred-work-with-tracker` per the
   12th specialty).
4. **accept-as-canon** (operator ratifies the validator misfire was
   structural; appends contra-precedent + decision row + amends the
   validator regex in a future mint).
5. **escalate-to-blocker-tracker** (cannot be dispositioned in-chat;
   mints `_blockers/<slug>-tracker.md` per
   [`akos-conflict-surfacing-and-blocker-trackers.mdc`](akos-conflict-surfacing-and-blocker-trackers.mdc)).

When findings exceed 10, the agent splits the gates into 2
`AskQuestion` batches (per inline-ratify-craft Principle 5 batching
guidance). Time-box recovery applies only to reversible dispositions per
`akos-inline-ratification.mdc` §"Time-box recovery"; irreversible
dispositions NEVER auto-default.

## RULE 6 — Browser-evidence audit-trail bar (when browser UAT is in scope)

When a closure UAT includes browser UAT (per
[`akos-planning-traceability.mdc`](akos-planning-traceability.mdc)
§"UAT evidence contract"), §3.4 of the report MUST include the
Playwright-MCP + audit-trail pattern: screenshot + accessibility-snapshot
+ sha256 + timestamp at each decision point, saved under
`artifacts/uat-screenshots/<initiative-slug>-<YYYY-MM-DD>/` with a
sha256 manifest sidecar. Code-evidence fallback (cite file + line range)
is acceptable when operator credentials are unavailable mid-session;
verdict in that row marks `CODE-EVIDENCE` (not `PASS`) to preserve the
live-walk distinction.

API logs / pytest output alone do not satisfy the browser-evidence bar
per the 2026 Playwright-MCP audit pattern grounding.

## RULE 7 — Sibling-repo deploy verification (when applicable)

When a closure UAT's parent initiative shipped work to a sibling
repository (per [`REPOSITORY_REGISTRY.csv`](../../docs/references/hlk/v3.0/Admin/O5-1/People/Compliance/canonicals/REPOSITORY_REGISTRY.csv))
that triggered a deploy, §3 mechanical evidence MUST include the
deploy-class verification: deploy ID + source sha + state (READY /
ERROR / BUILDING) verified via vendor MCP (per
[`akos-quality-fabric.mdc`](akos-quality-fabric.mdc) RULE 3 +
[`UAT_DISCIPLINE.md`](../../docs/references/hlk/v3.0/Admin/O5-1/People/canonicals/UAT_DISCIPLINE.md)
§3.7).

The Vercel `dpl_6uNfwjKVUNwqqd2MZ65vySkvd834` regression on 2026-05-20
(server-only-import poisoning client bundle; production-broken for ~14
hours) is the worked example proving local `tsc` PASS does not imply
vendor-side build PASS.

## RULE 8 — Specialty mint contract honored (binding)

This rule, the paired SOP, the paired runbook, the canonical doctrine
promotion, the cursor skill, and the process_list.csv row +
pattern_uat_class_taxonomy registry row land in the **same commit** (or
the next material commit) so the 12-specialty contract per
`akos-index-integrity.mdc` RULE 5 is honored. The mint quartet matches
the Wave M INTER_WAVE_REGRESSION precedent + the Wave N
INDEX_INTEGRITY precedent.

## When this rule does NOT apply

- One-off `reports/checkpoints/sc-*.md` agent self-checkpoints.
- Pre-2026-05-19 historical UAT reports (per canonical migration posture;
  forward-only bar).
- Operator-internal scratchpads + planning notes (not closure UAT).
- 1-3 phase quick-fix initiatives that close without a UAT report (the
  inline summary in the parent commit message suffices when the
  initiative is below the [`akos-planning-traceability.mdc`](akos-planning-traceability.mdc)
  §"UAT quality bar" applicability threshold).

## Self-discipline rules for agents

When closing an in-scope wave or initiative:

1. **Run the validator self-test before drafting the closure commit
   message.** `py scripts/validate_uat_report.py --self-test` must PASS.
2. **Run the full report validation before drafting the verdict line.**
   `py scripts/validate_uat_report.py --report <path>` emits the findings
   table.
3. **Compute findings count before posting the disposition AskQuestion
   batch.** ≤ 10 fits one batch; 11-20 splits into 2 batches; > 20
   triggers structural rework (the report itself is mis-shapen).
4. **For PASS-WITH-FOLLOWUP verdicts, fill `verdict_followup_rationale`
   inline before commit.** The rationale names the PWF class + tracker
   path + closure-target ETA. Empty rationale is the false-PASS
   anti-pattern the 12th specialty (D-IH-86-CX) exists to prevent.
5. **For amendments, populate `verdict_history`.** Cite prior verdict +
   prior date + reason for amendment. Cite the amending decision ID.
6. **For RULE 6 browser-evidence rows, capture artifacts + sha256
   manifest in the same commit as the UAT report.** Don't promise
   evidence in a follow-up; the audit trail decays the moment the
   render-state is lost.
7. **For RULE 7 deploy verification, run the vendor-MCP call AT
   closure time.** A pre-mint deploy state can have regressed by the
   time the operator reviews; the closure UAT must reflect the actual
   current vendor state.

